## 3. Project Structure

```
fintrack-ai/
├── client/src/
│   ├── pages/          ← Feature pages (Dashboard, Categories, Transactions, AIChat, Investments, Reports)
│   ├── components/     ← Reusable components (DashboardLayout, shadcn/ui)
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── trpc.ts     ← tRPC client binding
│   │   └── utils.ts    ← cn() helper + legacy utilities (kept for backward compat)
│   ├── App.tsx         ← Routes + ThemeProvider
│   └── index.css       ← Global design tokens (OKLCH colors, Inter font)
├── server/
│   ├── routers.ts      ← All tRPC procedures (split by domain)
│   ├── db.ts           ← Drizzle query helpers (one function per operation)
│   └── _core/          ← Framework plumbing (DO NOT EDIT)
├── drizzle/
│   └── schema.ts       ← Source of truth for all DB tables
├── shared/
│   ├── const.ts        ← Shared constants (COOKIE_NAME, etc.)
│   ├── types.ts        ← Shared TypeScript types
│   ├── date/index.ts   ← Date utilities (todayString, formatDate, getCurrentMonthYear...)
│   └── currency/index.ts ← Money utilities (formatVND, parseMoneyText, getBudgetProgressColor...)
└── docs/ai/            ← AI assistant documentation (architecture, conventions, data model, known issues)
```

---

## 4. Domain Modules

The app is organized into 8 feature domains. Each domain has:
- A router section in `server/routers.ts`
- Query helpers in `server/db.ts`
- A page in `client/src/pages/`

| Domain | Router prefix | Page | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| Auth | `auth.*` | — | OAuth login/logout, session management |
| Category | `category.*` | `Categories.tsx` | CRUD for income/expense categories |
| Transaction | `transaction.*` | `Transactions.tsx` | Manual and AI-assisted transaction entry |
| Budget | `category.recalcBudgets` | `Categories.tsx` | Budget limits with color engine |
| AI Chat | `ai.*` | `AIChat.tsx` | Vietnamese NLP transaction recording |
| Investment | `investment.*` | `Investments.tsx` | Gold/silver/savings/lending portfolio |
| Market | `market.*` | Dashboard + Investments | Gold/silver price fetching with 5-min cache |
| Report | `report.*` | `Reports.tsx` | Monthly breakdown, YoY comparison |
| Dashboard | Uses report + category | `Dashboard.tsx` | Summary widgets + market ticker |

---

## 5. Critical Coding Rules

### ALWAYS follow these patterns:

**1. Filter by userId in every DB query**
```typescript
// ✅ Always include userId filter
.where(and(eq(transactions.userId, userId), eq(transactions.isDeleted, false)))
```

**2. Date fields are varchar(10) strings — NEVER Date objects**
```typescript
// ✅ Correct
const transactionDate = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]; // "2026-03-12"
// ❌ Wrong
const transactionDate = new Date(); // causes DB type error
```

**3. Decimal DB columns return as strings — always Number() before math**
```typescript
// ✅ Correct
const pct = Number(budget.pctUsed);
// ❌ Wrong
const pct = budget.pctUsed * 100; // NaN
```

**4. Soft delete only — never hard delete**
```typescript
// ✅ Correct
await db.update(transactions).set({ isDeleted: true }).where(...)
// ❌ Wrong
await db.delete(transactions).where(...)
```

**5. After any transaction mutation, recalc budgets**
```typescript
// In db.ts after insert/update/delete of expense transactions:
await recalcBudgetSpent(categoryId);
```

**6. Invalidate all affected queries after mutations**
```typescript
// In client after transaction create/delete:
utils.transaction.list.invalidate();
utils.category.list.invalidate();
utils.report.monthly.invalidate();
utils.report.yoy.invalidate();
```

**7. Money inputs must use thousand-separator pattern**
```typescript
// Use Intl.NumberFormat("vi-VN") for display; store raw integer in state
const handleAmountChange = (e) => {
  const raw = e.target.value.replace(/\./g, "").replace(/[^0-9]/g, "");
  setAmount(parseInt(raw) || 0);
  setDisplayAmount(raw ? new Intl.NumberFormat("vi-VN").format(parseInt(raw)) : "");
};
```

